JOHANNESBURG Newcomers are leading the nominees' pack for this year s South African Music Awards (SAMA).Young rapper Nasty C is top of the list with six nods.Hot on his heels is another rapper, Kwesta with five nominations.SAMA22: Nathi, Emtee, Black Coffee among big winnersAnother new kid on the block and former Idols SA contestant Amanda Black, bagged four nominations.Under the theme, I live music, the Samas are returning to the Sun City Superbowl on 26 May.* Watch Nontobeko Sibisi's video report in the gallery above.eNCA